    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-21T03:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-21T03:30:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">6S9.90D/4–2151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Pakistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-21T14:00:00+05:30"
                            >April 21, 1951—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>988. For McGhee. Re Embs 960, Apr 14.<note n="1" xml:id="d327fn1">Not printed,
                        but see the editorial note, <ref target="#pg_1959">p. 1959</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> in conversation this p. m. hoped his
                    reply ref <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 661, Apr 18 wld be
                    considered as an acceptance of the US Nov 6 <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> and
                    regretted its unfavorable reception. After lengthy discussion based largely on
                    his recollection of conversation with McGhee and an exposition of the points in
                        <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> under ref, the <gloss
                        target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> authorized me to say his govt accepts
                    para 3 (b) of Dept’s proposal, i.e. <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> accepts
                    unconditionally first three points of US approach of Nov 6 and reaffirms its
                    attitude on point four of the Nov 6 approach as expressed in its memo of Apr
                    14.</p>
                <p>Shld the Dept still consider this reaffirmation a counterproposal he nevertheless
                    wld be pleased to have the Dept submit it to the Afghans and wld welcome the
                    Dept’s indication of their reaction to it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
